── WHAT IS SHOWSHAK ────────────────────────────────────────────

ShowShak is a cross-platform streaming discovery app.
It is NOT a streaming service. It is NOT a social media app.
It is the discovery layer that sits between the user and all
streaming platforms (Netflix, Prime, Disney+, JioHotstar, etc.)

The core loop:
  Curator posts a short clip recommending a show/movie
  → User watches, feels something, trusts the curator
  → User taps "Watch It" → goes to the streaming platform

The product lives in a category that doesn't exist yet:
  "Trust-based, creator-curated, action-oriented discovery."

Closest references for mental model:
  - Letterboxd (film culture + human taste) but with action
  - TikTok/Reels (short vertical clips) but with intent
  - None of the above — ShowShak is its own thing


── PRODUCT PHILOSOPHY ──────────────────────────────────────────

1. CREATOR FIRST, SHOW SECOND
   The curator builds the connection. The clip is their pitch.
   We do NOT show the show title upfront on the clip — the user
   should connect with the curator before knowing the title.
   If they already saw it, we lose them. If they trust the
   curator first, they'll watch anything recommended.

2. FAMILIAR BUT SHOWSHAK
   We take patterns users already know (vertical scroll, fire/
   like, save, share) and give them streaming-native meaning.
   Nothing should feel like "oh it's another TikTok" or
   "oh it's another Netflix." Familiar interactions, ShowShak soul.

3. FIRE = THIS IS LIT
   The "like" equivalent is 🔥 Fire. Not a heart. Not a thumbs up.
   Fire means "this show/movie is genuinely great" — specific
   to the entertainment context. The fire icon and color family
   (orange → red) intentionally match the ShowShak brand palette.

4. WATCH IT IS THE CLIMAX
   Every clip builds to one moment: the user deciding to watch.
   "Watch It" (not "Watch Now") — decisive, personal, like a
   friend telling you what to do. It is the most important
   interaction in the entire product. The CTA has a breathing
   glow animation and flashes when a user fires a clip (fire
   energy converts to watch action — emotional peak → decision).

5. CONTENT SIGNALS ONLY — NO SOCIAL SIGNALS
   We show: genre tags, language tag, creator caption (2 lines)
   We do NOT show: show title on clip, IMDb score, platform badge
   on clip, follower counts, view counts.
   The platform reveal lives ONLY in the Watch It sheet.

6. CURATORS, NOT INFLUENCERS
   People who post clips are curators / tastemakers — people
   whose taste you trust. The product should always treat them
   as taste authorities, not content creators chasing views.


── VOCABULARY ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Fire         = like/heart equivalent
  Watch It     = the primary CTA (never "Watch Now")
  Watchlist    = saved shows (was "Wishlist" — now Watchlist)
  Curator      = person who posts clips (not "creator/influencer")
  Clip         = short recommendation video (not "reel/video")
  Feed         = the vertical clip scroll page
  Discover     = the search/browse/mood page
  Fires count  = formatted with fmtFires() e.g. 1.2k not 1200


── TECH STACK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Pure HTML + CSS + Vanilla JS — zero frameworks, zero build tools
  Google Fonts: Bebas Neue (display/headings) + DM Sans (body)
  No npm, no React, no Tailwind, no bundler
  Runs directly in browser via VS Code Live Server extension
  Target: website prototype → handed off to app developers later


