── SHARED CSS CLASSES TO REUSE ─────────────────────────────────

  Layout:     .ss-layout (main content area with sidebar offset)
  Sidebar:    .sidebar, .nav-item, .nav-item-icon, .nav-item-label
  Mobile nav: .mobile-bottom-nav, .mob-nav-item, .mob-nav-icon
  Tags:       .tag (genre/language pill — red family)
  Toast:      #ss-toast (auto-created by shared.js, call ssToast())
  Sheet:      #watch-sheet, #watch-sheet-overlay (Watch It bottom sheet)
  Animation:  @keyframes ss-fadeUp (entry animation for page elements)


── SHARED JS FUNCTIONS TO REUSE ────────────────────────────────

  ssToast(msg)              show a toast notification
  ssOpenSheet(show)         open the Watch It bottom sheet
  ssCloseSheet()            close the Watch It bottom sheet
  ssHandleWatchNow(p, t)    platform selected callback
  ssShare(show)             Web Share API or clipboard fallback
  ssPageFadeIn()            smooth page entry (auto-runs on load)
  ssScrollToTop(elementId)  smooth scroll to top of element
  fmtFires(n)               format number: 1240 → "1.2k"
  showToast(msg)            alias for ssToast
  scrollFeedToTop()         alias for ssScrollToTop('feed')


── FEED PAGE KEY BEHAVIOURS ────────────────────────────────────

  - Vertical snap scroll, one clip per viewport height
  - IntersectionObserver fires syncRail() + animateRailIn() per clip
  - Desktop: action rail (Fire, Save, Share, Watch It pill) sits
    to the right of the clip column, positioned by positionRail()
  - Watch It pill: breathing glow animation, fire-flash on fire
  - Mobile: action rail overlaid on clip right side, Watch It
    button above bottom nav
  - Double-tap: fire burst animation at tap position + auto-fire
  - Single tap: pause indicator
  - SHOWS data needs: id, title, year, genre[], lang, runtime,
    season, synopsis, caption, creator{name,letter,bg},
    litCount, platforms[], platLabel, platColor, platRgb, bg


── DISCOVER PAGE KEY BEHAVIOURS ────────────────────────────────

  - Search bar with recent search dropdown
  - Mood pills (8 moods) filter the clip grid
  - Platform chips filter by streaming service
  - Featured clips: horizontal scroll row
  - For You: 2-column grid
  - Results view replaces default view on search/filter
  - CLIPS data needs: same as SHOWS + mood[], platAbbr


── WHAT MAKES SHOWSHAK DIFFERENT ───────────────────────────────

  NOT Instagram/TikTok: clips are not the destination, they are
  a window. The show IS the destination. Curators are not
  influencers — they are taste authorities.

  NOT Netflix: we don't own the content. We send users TO the
  platform. We are the bridge, not the destination.

  THE GAP WE FILL: human taste + cross-platform + action.
  "Your most trusted film-obsessed friend, with a platform."


